# 21. Leo/need

Saki: Playing in SEKAI was awesome, right?
Ichika: Yeah, it felt so good. It was perfect. Just perfect.
Shiho: Look up. It's not SEKAI-level amazing, but the stars look pretty good here too.
Honami: You're right, they're so pretty! Just like back then...
Ichika: ...Yeah.
Saki: I feel like I'm still walking on clouds! This isn't a dream, right?
Ichika: It's real. The song we played, and what we're feeling now, it's all real.
Shiho: Yeah. And we still have school tomorrow.
Saki: Guh... Shiho, don't kill the vibe like that!
Honami: Hehe. It's time to head home.
Ichika: Take care. See you at school tomorrow!
Saki: Sure! See you, guys!
Honami: .....
Honami's Classmate A: Ho-na-mi! Morning!
Honami: Morning. There's something I need to tell you... Do you have a few minutes?
Honami's Classmate B: Yeah, sure. What's up?
Honami's Classmate A: Gosh, I had no idea.
Honami's Classmate B: Thanks for sharing this with us, Honami.
Honami: I'm sorry I kept it secret for so long...
Honami's Classmate A: No, no, it's understandable. We were worried about you, you know? You seemed so sad lately.
Honami's Classmate B: Yeah! But you didn't look like you wanted to talk, so we didn't know what to do about it.
Honami's Classmate A: Thank you for opening up. And...sorry I said those mean things about Hinomori.
Honami: No worries! Shiho is actually very nice. I could introduce you to her, if you'd like.
Honami's Classmate B: Sure, I'd like to get to know her! By the way, do you guys have any gigs planned yet?
Honami: No, we only just started... But once we do, you're invited!
Honami's Classmate A: Cool! I'm already hyped to see you on stage!
Honami: (If I'd only known it would be this easy.)
Honami: (I should have been honest with my friends. It was so silly of me to think they wouldn't understand.)
Ichika: Do you really think it's okay for us to be spying on Honami?
Saki: Shush! She'll hear you!
Shiho: We could've just waited for her to tell us how it went later. Why did I let you drag me along like this...
Saki: I was so worried, I couldn't sit still! It looks like the talk went well, thankfully!
Ichika: It will be nice if her friends can come to our gigs. I'm also glad Honami corrected their misconceptions about Shiho.
Shiho: Meh, I don't care either way.
Ichika: But I do! I want more people to discover that you actually have a great personality.
Shiho: You're making me cringe. Anyway, classes are about to start. We'd better go.
Saki: Now that school is done, it's time for a band strategy meeting!
Shiho: For a what?
Saki: You know, we have to decide on a lot of things! Our band name for starters! Do you have any ideas?
Ichika: Why are you looking at me?
Saki: I thought you'd be the expert when it comes to inventing cool names!
Honami: Do you have something in mind, Ichika?
Ichika: No, I haven't thought about it yet, but we should come up with something original that would suit us all.
Shiho: Maybe something to do with stars? That meteor shower in the Leo constellation is an important memory for all of us.
Saki: I like that! Shiho, I didn't know you had a sentimental streak!
Shiho: Now I regret saying anything...
Saki: Didn't that meteor shower have a name?
Honami: I told you back then, Saki...
Honami: It was the Leonids. Or maybe we could go with the French name? It's um...Les Léonides.
Ichika: That's nice. Sounds kind of like Leo need.
Saki: Yeah, let's spell that part need! To mean that everyone's needed!
Ichika: You want it written...like this?
Honami: Leoneed? I think it's good.
Saki: Wait, I can make it better! How about Leo/need?
Shiho: What's the slash for?
Saki: Hehe... It's a shooting star!
Honami: Having a shooting star in our name is a wonderful idea!
Shiho: It's just a slash but...I guess I can kind of see it now.
Ichika: Okay, guys! We have a band name! And by the way...
Ichika: I wrote lyrics for a song Saki composed earlier.
Shiho: You guys have already written a song? Nice.
Honami: That's amazing! Can I see the lyrics?
Ichika: Uh, maybe later? It's kind of embarrassing to have them read in front of me...
Ichika: But I hope we can all perform it... together.
Shiho: Let's do that at Leo/need's first practice session.
Saki: Yay!
Honami: Okay! So...this is the beginning of Leo/need.
Ichika: Yeah. This is going to be great, everyone.
Miku: I'm so happy that they found their true feelings.
Luka: Yes. They became a really pretty song. You seemed to like it a great deal.
Miku: I... I just really enjoyed singing together with them.
Miku: I wonder what songs they're going to create next. It'll be exciting to find out!
Luka: Miku, look up at the sky.
Miku: Oh...
Miku: What a beautiful shooting star!
